{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-work-post-js","path":"/design/Particle Granulator (Alpha)/index/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>An exploration of digital site-specificity, this project places the user in a chaotically-deterministic loop. Since parameters change with each iteration, they must take time to figure out how the ecosystem works, and then sensitively compose with it, rather than into it. I see this as engaging with the intersection of instrument design with theories of sound ecologies. I am also using some machine learning and controller mapping to achieve this.</p>\n<!-- Embed soundcloud player: -->\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"166\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1111733245&color=%23ff5500&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&show_comments=true&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=true\"></iframe><div style=\"font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;\"><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/ashnotketchup\" title=\"Ashnotketchup\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;\">Ashnotketchup</a> · <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/ashnotketchup/gfm-ep1-guitar-and-voice\" title=\"GFM Ep1 Guitar And Voice\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;\">GFM Ep1 Guitar And Voice</a></div>\n<!-- add link to grain fm -->\n<p>This project marks the second in my series “Grain FM”, an exploration of physical modelling and granular sampling/synthesis. In this particular manifestation, transients are mapped equidistantly about the unit circle, and then granularly sampled as controlled by weather data and gyroscopic controls.</p>\n<!-- TODO:Basically I want images to share the width, while being the same height, or on mobile to take the full width\n\nConvert this to parse just markdown images, this is too verbose \n -->\n<figure>\n    <div>\n        <div class=\"is-child\">\n            <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Green background with white particles swarming in a circle\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/ead0c9214f0a138b2c94c2b133169133/5a190/Particles-move.png\" srcset=\"/static/ead0c9214f0a138b2c94c2b133169133/772e8/Particles-move.png 200w,\n/static/ead0c9214f0a138b2c94c2b133169133/e17e5/Particles-move.png 400w,\n/static/ead0c9214f0a138b2c94c2b133169133/5a190/Particles-move.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n    </span>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"is-child\">\n            <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Green background with white particles swarming in an arc\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/6c7cd978e4a1c150f8b80b03f93fad36/5a190/Particles-move3.png\" srcset=\"/static/6c7cd978e4a1c150f8b80b03f93fad36/772e8/Particles-move3.png 200w,\n/static/6c7cd978e4a1c150f8b80b03f93fad36/e17e5/Particles-move3.png 400w,\n/static/6c7cd978e4a1c150f8b80b03f93fad36/5a190/Particles-move3.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n    </span>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n  <figcaption> ↑ One-thousand particles are distributed about the unit circle. Users can control grain playback by manipulating this visualisation</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<br>\nHere is a brief demo utilising a piano and the circle of fifths:\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/u7vPjRdDeAU?si=AyHCAZIPrei4nxW_&amp;controls=0\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\n<!-- does this work -->\n<p><a href=\"ParticleGranulator_Stereo.zip\">Download the patch + notes</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Particle Granulator (Alpha)","subtitle":null,"date":"Sunday, 1 October 2023","author":"Ash"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/design/Particle Granulator (Alpha)/index","breadcrumb":{"location":"/design/Particle Granulator (Alpha)/index/","crumbs":[{"pathname":"/","crumbLabel":"Home"},{"pathname":"/design","crumbLabel":"design"},{"pathname":"/design/Particle Granulator (Alpha)","crumbLabel":"Particle Granulator (Alpha)"},{"pathname":"/design/Particle Granulator (Alpha)/index","crumbLabel":"index"}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}